##### 66 Authorizing Mount Somers Domain Board to erect a public hall
    
*   (1) The Mount Somers Domain Board constituted pursuant to Part 2 of the Public Reserves and Domains Act 1908, is hereby authorized and empowered to erect a public hall on such part of the said domain as may be approved by the Minister of Lands.
    
    (2) The said Board may expend in respect of the cost of erection of the said public hall an amount not exceeding one thousand six hundred dollars, and any payment heretofore made by the Board for the said purpose shall be deemed to have been made under the authority of this section.
    
    (3) The said Board may charge for the hire, letting, or use of the said hall, and for admission thereto, such rent or rates as it may from time to time fix by resolution.
    
